RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY DOWNS RACE 8 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 85. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 13500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 (AB $5,000) OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $8,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 . Alberta Bred Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THE BEAT dueled for the early lead, contended the pace outside of PUMP THE BRAKES, gained the advantage entering the stretch and held. UPO saved ground early, gained quickly into the final turn, dug in through the final yards, and was up just in time for place. PUMP THE BRAKES vied inside for the lead then matched strides through the backstretch, steadied inside into the final turn, angled out to the two path, and was edged out before the wire. GRIGORO tracked from just off the rail, shifted three wide, and was unable to improve position in the stretch. LONESOME CAT unhurried early and showed a mild interest late. MAKE'N TRACKS trailed the field, and passed tiring foes. MANFORALLSEASONS failed to threaten. ALL THAT GOLD rated well off the dueling pair, and was done early. JOCKEY OBJECTION- An objection lodged by the rider of PUMP THE BRAKES against the rider of THE BEAT alleging interference in the far turn was not allowed.
